cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.HC

This paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it uses a method to detect statistically significant gender differences in language use in a large corpus of comments on Reddit. It also involves social media analysis (cs.SI) and data mining (cs.SD) techniques. Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cyberpsychology (cs.CY) as it explores gender differences in online behavior and interests.
